rComments: He's nice and tries to help you learn the language but don't take this this class w him if you're shy and don't like talking in a group of people you dont know bc he counts participation! He's very vague when explaining what he expects from you in terms of "participation" and doesn't adequately prepare you for tests bc he doesn't write them...

Loved this prof. I had Irmtraut Lyon last semester and barely learned anything because she was so intimidating. I have learned so much already from Kruger! Great guy, super helpful, he really wants you to learn. If you're taking German try your hardest to get him!!

I had him at Carleton, for beginner German. He is actually such an awesome prof and makes everyone feel really comfortable in class. Even when the material is more difficult he engages everyone in a very casual manner and gives instant corrections which makes learning German super easy! Love this prof. Funny and knowledgable about the culture.
Awesome teacher! Gives clear examples and makes learning German very interesting. Definitely recommend him. :)
Very friendly and approchable; he made a very comfortable environment for the students to learn german. Very understanding and accomodating. Overall, a great prof.

He was a good prof such that he was very accommodating for students, but he wasn't the most organized and fell behind in the course plan. He created a comfortable environment though which made him very approachable!

Good prof. Always answers emails in a timely manner. Very helpful. Would have preferred he be a little more well-versed on the cinema side as this was a German Cinema class but he knows his German history VERY WELL and his tangents are not boring to listen to. One midterm, 1 short paper, final. Answer 5 out of these 9 questions. Easy peasy!

Pretty easy prof. Quite easy to get 100% on the assignments (3 written assignments of 120 words). Exam/tests weren't too hard. No midterm. The only problem I had was the Vocab Quizzes, which ALWAYS used words that were barely mentioned in class. I literally failed every one of the 5 quizzes. Thank God they were only for your participation mark.
